# Copy to .env and adjust. Never commit .env.
# Synthetic seed data only; this project never touches real patient data.
#
# Defaults work as-is on Windows, so .env is optional there.

# --- Front-end ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Read from this file by Vite (see envDir in frontend/vite.config.ts).

# Where the API lives.
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5080

# The lab the stubbed session acts as, sent as the X-Lab-Id header on every request.
# Isolation is enforced on the server; this only chooses who you are, not what you may
# reach. Seeded labs: 1 = Central Lab, 2 = Westside Pathology Lab.
#
# Switch to 2 to watch Central Lab's manifests become unreachable.
VITE_LAB_ID=1

# --- Backend ------------------------------------------------------------------
# The API reads configuration from appsettings.json and the environment — it does not
# read this file. The value below is the default already baked into appsettings.json for
# Windows; to point the API elsewhere, export it into the environment instead:
#
#   export ConnectionStrings__SpecimenCheckIn="Server=localhost,1433;Database=SpecimenCheckIn;User Id=sa;Password=Local_Dev_Pa55w0rd!;TrustServerCertificate=True"
#
# ConnectionStrings__SpecimenCheckIn=Server=(localdb)\MSSQLLocalDB;Database=SpecimenCheckIn;Trusted_Connection=True;TrustServerCertificate=True
